text:
DKC2 has one of my favorite video game soundtracks ever. It's got a lot of solid songs, and listening to the full soundtrack is always a delightful treat. So, listening to Jib Jig at the beginning of the game/full soundtrack listening session is an incredible treat. It really sets the atmosphere very well.

It's interesting how this song makes me feel incredibly nostalgic and takes me right back to the 90s, even though I never grew up with this game as a kid.

text: The beginning of this game sets you right into the amazing atmosphere it delivers: pirate ship, heavy rain and wind with a memorable little theme by David Wise. It makes you want to jump in and forget about everything else, taking it all in. The DKC series is one my favorites, especially since the newer games continue to be just as awesome, with arguably even better level design on Retro's part. Stil, there's something about the art/graphics in the SNES trilogy that I miss, providing a very unique atmosphere that isn't as heavy in the newer entries.
